Russian Grain Producer Razgulay Plans 57% Increase in Plantings

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-04-08T12:00:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/russian-grain-producer-razgulay-plans-57-increase-in-plantings.html
Russian grains and sugar producer
 OAO Razgulay Group  plans to increase plantings by 57 percent in
five years to 503,000 hectares (1.2 million acres) by 2015.  Refined rice output will climb 89 percent to 409,000 metric
tons in 2015 from 216,000 tons in 2010, Razgulay spokeswoman
Ekaterina Agibalova said today. That includes production of rice
grit, flour and starch. Refined sugar-beet production is
forecast to jump to 5.94 million tons from 2.85 million tons
while sugar output climbs to 850,000 tons from 368,000 tons,
according to the company.  To contact the reporter on this story: Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow
   msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Claudia
Carpenter at   ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  